[1] Macedonia
Date: Sat 9 Feb 2019
Source: China.org.cn, a Xinhua report [edited]
http://www.china.org.cn/world/Off_the_Wire/2019-02/09/content_74449078.htm


The Macedonian Health Minister Venko Filipce confirmed on [Fri 8 Feb 2019] the death of a 6-month-old baby related to measles. According to Filipce, the baby was under treatment for lung complications and was not vaccinated.

The minister said vaccination in Macedonia should continue in order to strengthen the immunity of the population after the significant drop on vaccination coverage in 2014.

Filipce also confirmed that 2 children are treated for lung complications but are not in life-threatening conditions.

The minister made the remarks after his visit at the Neurology Clinic in Skopje.

On [2 Jan 2019], the Health Ministry in Macedonia declared the outbreak of measles in the capital of Skopje.

