[5] Pacific Northwest [Canada (Vancouver), Washington (Clark County), Oregon]
Date: Sat 9 Feb 2019
Source: Oregon Live [abridged, edited]
https://www.oregonlive.com/business/2019/02/2-more-unvaccinated-children-bring-vancouver-area-measles-outbreak-to-58.html


Two more unvaccinated children were diagnosed with measles [Fri 8 Feb 2019]. That brings the Clark County cases up to 53. Outside of the county, that number is 58, including 4 people in Oregon and one man in King County.

All of the measles cases in this outbreak have been traced to the same wild strain the of the measles virus from Eastern Europe.

Clark County Public Health Officer Dr. Alan Melnick said last week that he and his office have only started to try to figure out where the outbreak started. So far, they have been focused on containing it and treating people who need it.

[Byline: Molly Harbarger]

