[6] Thailand
Date: Fri 08 Feb 2019
Source: Outbreak News Today [abridged, edited]
http://outbreaknewstoday.com/measles-thailand-600-cases-first-month-41403/


In a follow-up on the measles situation in Thailand, health officials have reported 613 cases from 47 provinces through [4 Feb 2019]. Of the total, 109 cases involved complications and 2 deaths were recorded.

The provinces with the highest rates of cases include Narathiwat, Pattani, Songkla, Yala and Petchburi.

More than 5000 cases were reported in 2018, primarily in the southern parts of the country.

