[11] Australia (Canberra)
Date: Fri 8 Feb 2019, 5.47 PM
Source: Canberra Times [abridged, edited]
https://www.canberratimes.com.au/national/act/third-case-of-measles-confirmed-in-canberra-since-december-20190208-p50wnb.html


The 3rd case of measles within 2 months has been confirmed in Canberra with authorities urging the community to be aware of symptoms.

ACT public health physician Dr. Kerryn Coleman said the resident acquired the infection on a recent overseas trip. It is not linked to the previous 2 cases.

The person attended Canberra Airport between 10am and 11am on [Sun 10 Feb 2019] while infectious."Anyone who was at the Canberra Airport on [Sun 10 Feb 2019] should be aware for signs and symptoms of measles from now until [24 Feb 2019]," Dr. Coleman said.

[Byline: Daniella White]

