[12] Australia (South Australia)
Date: Thu 14 Feb 2019, 2:05 AM
Source: Adelaide Now [edited]

She advised the measles vaccine should be considered while travelling overseas and South Australians should check they had received 2 doses of the vaccination, especially those born in the late 1960s to mid-1980s.

Two measles cases were reported last year [2018].

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://www.adelaidenow.com.au/news/south-australia/health-warning-20yearold-man-contracts-measles/news-


A South Australian man has contracted measles -- the 2nd case reported this year.

A health alert has been issued for Western Clinic Medical Centre and the Australian Clinical Laboratory collection centre inside the clinic at Torrensville where the 20-year-old man was while he was infectious. [See URL for locations infected individual attended]

SA Health Communicable Disease Control Branch director Dr. Louise Flood said there have been multiple cases of measles notified in Australia this year [2019]. "Most cases have been acquired overseas, but some have been 2ary cases passed on to other within Australia," she said.

She advised the measles vaccine should be considered while travelling overseas and South Australians should check they had received 2 doses of the vaccination, especially those born in the late 1960s to mid-1980s.

Two measles cases were reported last year [2018].

